Galba had but one legion, and Vindex's 100,000 men were not Roman citizensÍ¾ much therefore depended on the action of the legions of Germany. Verginius Rufus, legatus of the Upper Province, marched on Vesontio and there held a conference with Vindex. Through some misunderstanding, Verginius' men attacked the army of Vindex, killing 20,000 and dispersing the rest, on which Vindex slew him- self. Verginius returned to his province, and refused to allow either himself or anyone else to be proclaimed emperor, except by nomination of senate and people.
